-- Nigeria's foreign reserves rise marginally to $37.26 bln by June 26
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 10:08AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, June 30 (Reuters) - Nigeria's foreign exchange reserves <NGFXR=ECI> rose marginally to $37.26 billion on June 26, up 0.18 percent month-on-month, from $37.19 billion in May, central bank data showed on Monday.

